Description: Fragment of handle at shoulder join of A pottery transport amphora. Stamped at join. Clay coarse red-brown; dark brown core. Ovoid stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 55, 35 or 110, 5. Name Elaitas.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1702)
